	abstract = {The current research investigates the effects of disclosure (versus non-disclosure) of AI-generated content and source type in travel destination-related advertising posts on consumers' attitudes and behavioral intentions. Study 1 (N = 395) examined how AI disclosure effects on consumer responses varied across four source types (business versus government organization versus non-government organization versus social media influencer). In Study 2 (N = 201), we investigated the effects of human social media influencers posting AI-generated content with or without disclosure. We found evidence for the effectiveness of the disclosure in recognizing the AI-generated content for the advertising posts by a hospitality business and social media influencers. Disclosing the AI-generated origin of social media influencers' advertising posts lowered brand credibility, attitude, and purchase intention. Attitudes towards AI moderate the relation between the recognition of the AI origin of the post and brand credibility.},
